question_results.context: It costs US $205 to take the GRE test. ETS provides financial aid to those GRE applicants who prove economic hardship. Economic hardship refers to difficulty caused by having too little money or too few resources. Tom lives in a single-parent family. His dad has been out of work for more than a year.
question_results.question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? It cost below US $300 to take the GRE test.
question_results.combined_program:
set(auto).
assign(max_seconds, 5).
assign(max_mem, 1024).
# Predicates:
Cost(x, y) ::: It costs y to take test x.
GRE(x) ::: x is the GRE test.
Provides(x, y, z) ::: x provides y to z.
FinancialAid(x) ::: x is financial aid.
Applicant(x) ::: x is an applicant.
GREApplicant(x) ::: x is a GRE applicant.
Prove(x, y) ::: x proves y.
EconomicHardship(x) ::: x is economic hardship.
RefersTo(x, y) ::: x refers to y.
Difficulty(x) ::: x is a difficulty.
CausedBy(x, y) ::: x is caused by y.
HavingTooLittleMoney(x) ::: x is having too little money.
HavingTooFewResources(x) ::: x is having too few resources.
LivesIn(x, y) ::: x lives in y.
SingleParentFamily(x) ::: x is a single-parent family.
Person(x) ::: x is a person.
Dad(x, y) ::: x is the dad of y.
OutOfWork(x, y) ::: x has been out of work for y.
Year(x) ::: x is a year.
Tom(x) ::: x is Tom.

# Premises:
Cost(GRE, 205USD).
∀x (GREApplicant(x) ∧ Prove(x, EconomicHardship) → Provides(ETS, FinancialAid, x)).
∀x (EconomicHardship(x) ↔ (RefersTo(x, Difficulty) ∧ (CausedBy(x, HavingTooLittleMoney) ∨ CausedBy(x, HavingTooFewResources)))).
Person(tom).
LivesIn(tom, tom_family).
SingleParentFamily(tom_family).
Dad(tom_dad, tom).
OutOfWork(tom_dad, year_more_than_one).
Applicant(tom).
GREApplicant(tom).
Tom(tom).
HasBeenOutOfWorkFor(tom_dad, year_more_than_one).

# Definitions:
# This definition directly links the conditions described for Tom to the concept of EconomicHardship for him.
EconomicHardship(tom) :-
    LivesIn(tom, tom_family),
    SingleParentFamily(tom_family),
    ∃ DadOfTom (Dad(DadOfTom, tom)),
    HasBeenOutOfWorkFor(DadOfTom, year_more_than_one).

# This definition connects the fact that Tom meets the criteria for EconomicHardship to him proving it.
Prove(tom, EconomicHardship) :-
    EconomicHardship(tom).

# Conclusion:
Cost(GRE_Test, 205) ∧ (205 < 300)
